sub_title: R&D | Researcher | Product Developer | Chemistry | PhD
summary:
Independent, proactive, science enthusiast and looking for a meaningful impact in chemistry. I acquired experience in chemical synthesis, analysis and characterization of complex chemical structures as well as investigation of reaction mechanisms. During my PhD (Chemistry and Nanotechnology under the supervision of Nobel Prize Laureate Ben L. Feringa), I learned to perform research at a high research level in a dynamic and diverse environment. I could develop strong communication and supervision skills in years of tutoring and guiding students and through frequent presentations in international conferences.
After a year of lab-teaching at the University of Groningen, I decided to take the next step and I am now working as Lecturer and Researcher at Saxion - University of Applied Sciences.
